    <body>&lt;p&gt;I finally got my first prototype which I&apos;ll show at the Embedded World&lt;br /&gt; in a week.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; It&apos;s a voltage conversion base board which enables you to connect a 5V&lt;br /&gt; Arduino shield to a Beagle Bone Black.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; What you can see here[1] is a Grove shield connected to it. Now you can&lt;br /&gt; connect many different sensors/actors[2] to the BBB.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; Left from the BBB are even more pins on Grove connectors (with 5V&lt;br /&gt; conversion) and lots of jumpers to jumper what goes where.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt;[1] &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.reliableembeddedsystems.com/images/Hw4SWppl.jpg&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noreferrer&quot;&gt;http://www.reliableembeddedsystems.com/images/Hw4SWppl.jpg&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt; [2] &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.seeedstudio.com/wiki/Grove_System&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noreferrer&quot;&gt;http://www.seeedstudio.com/wiki/Grove_System&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</body>
